@startuml multi-hop-authorization-sequence
' Editable UML master for the multi-hop authorization sequence diagram (Trust Protocol §2.3).
' Render to SVG with a white background:  plantuml -tsvg multi-hop-authorization-sequence.puml
' The committed .svg is a hand-tuned render of this master; re-running plantuml
' produces an equivalent diagram. Keep both committed (see diagrams/README.md).
' Patent note: for the filing, re-render in black/white line art and add reference
' numerals (the step numbers (1)-(6) below map to method-claim steps).

title Multi-Hop Authorization — Trust Protocol §2.3

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor Human
participant "Agent A" as A
participant "Agent B" as B

Human -> A : (1) request\n[OAuth token, scope = S_h]
activate A
note left of A
  (2) §2.1 authorize human
  required_A ⊆ S_h
end note

A -> B : (3) invoke upstream\n[passport + presentation proof, scope = S_a]
activate B
note left of B
  (4) §2.2 authorize Agent A
  1. ceiling: proof.scopes ⊆ A.passport.scopes
  2. required_B ⊆ proof.scopes
end note

B --> A : (5) result
deactivate B
A --> Human : (6) result
deactivate A

note across
  Two independent authorizations. S_a is bounded only by Agent A's passport
  ceiling, not by S_h. Each hop keeps its own audit record.
end note

@enduml
